mb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTkct_GGwwp8sQmrdZyibP4BfHJ2V5YohU_CQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:472;s:6:"height";i:800;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/246994360802377318/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:61:{i:0;s:27:"Standard Dining Room Table.";i:1;s:88:"6 rows Similar to table height there is no definite industry standard for chair heights.";i:2;s:158:"Ignoring everything else for the moment the realistic minimum distance between the chair seat and table top is around 24cm with the maximum being around 30cm.";i:3;s:25:"The ideal is around 26cm.";i:4;s:70:"Most modern chairs have their seat height set at around 50cm from the.";i:5;s:178:"Counter height tables and chairs have the same functionality as dining height tables and chairs but are slightly raised for a different aesthetic and in some cases space savings.";i:6;s:136:"A counter height table is typically 34 to 36 inches tall and can be paired with counter height chairs or stools at 24 to 26 inches tall.";i:7;s:81:"Counter height chairs and stools can also be used if you have an outdoor counter.";i:8;s:89:"Counter height tables and chairs measure 6 inches less than pub height tables and chairs.";i:9;s:60:"This difference is not easily discernible without measuring.";i:10;s:127:"Always measure to check what height your table or chair is as pub and counter height tables and chairs cannot be used together.";i:11;s:48:"Tip Pub tables are also comfortable to stand at.";i:12;s:103:"The standard height for a garden table is often the same as a dining table sitting around 28 - 30 high.";i:13;s:89:"This allows you to comfortably sit in a chair and have your arms be level with the table.";i:14;s:43:"With adjustable desks height is no problem.";i:15;s:78:"Otherwise something can be placed under the table for a table that is too low.";i:16;s:71:"If the table is too high the seat height of the chair must be adjusted.";i:17;s:43:"If this doesnt help a footrest can be used.";i:18;s:32:"The correct height of the table.";i:19;s:119:"In contrast a standard dining table chair measures anywhere from 16 to 19 inches from the floor to the top of the seat.";i:20;s:100:"As you can see in the above section the seat heights for all of our chairs fall within these ranges.";i:21;s:56:"Again just look for a gap of 9 to 13 inches between the.";i:22;s:68:"The overall height of the chair will depend on the style and design.";i:23;s:50:"How much space do you need for a restaurant chair.";i:24;s:142:"A good rule of thumb is to allow 24 inches or two feet for every person at the table for quick serve fast casual or casual dining restaurants.";i:25;s:48:"Fine dining restaurants for more room per diner.";i:26;s:162:"The general rule for tables in early care and education classrooms is the space between the seat of the chair and the underside of the table should be 7-8 inches.";i:27;s:177:"Thats just the right amount of space for children to be able to fit their legs under the table and it also ensures that the table is low enough for children to comfortably rest.";i:28;s:72:"The two most common dining chair seat height ranges are 18 23 and 24 26.";i:29;s:84:"This is because chairs are most often paired with these most common types of tables.";i:30;s:90:"Standard-height tables which are 28 30 high or counter-height tables which are 34 36 high.";i:31;s:110:"For all tables we recommend allowing for at least 12 of space between the seat of your chair and the tabletop.";i:32;s:124:"As a rule of thumb table chairs should have between 8 and 12 inches of legroom between the seat and the bottom of the table.";i:33;s:34:"If you use mismatched chairs with.";i:34;s:75:"Below weve highlighted the height ranges for each from shortest to tallest.";i:35;s:251:"Standard Chair Height is 16 23H at the seat Counter Height is 24 27H at the seat Bar Height is 28 33H at the seat First things first we recommend that you first pull out your tape measure and start measuring the height of your bar table or countertop.";i:36;s:52:"It also feels modern to have less height on a chair.";i:37;s:116:"With shorter chairs I would use great lamps on a sideboard pattern in wallpaper or a great centerpiece on the table.";i:38;s:58:"Finally it is not always cheaper to reupholster chairs vs.";i:39;s:98:"Make sure you really love the chairs before you put money into rebuilding and reupholstering them.";i:40;s:344:"As nouns the difference between chair and table is that chair is an item of furniture used to sit on or in comprising a seat legs back and sometimes arm rests for use by one person compare stool couch sofa settee loveseat and bench while table is an item of furniture with a flat top surface raised above the ground usually on one or more legs.";i:41;s:48:"As verbs the difference between chair and table.";i:42;s:104:"Without the seats comfort heights measure 16 to 18 inches while with seats they measure 17 to 19 inches.";i:43;s:231:"Standard height measures 14 to 15 inches without the seat and 15 to 16 inches with the seat Following is a table of showing a summary of differences in terms of features and usage Comparing chair height and standard height toilets.";i:44;s:101:"A bar-height table is even taller than a counter-height table standing between 40 and 42 inches tall.";i:45;s:92:"Bar tables are generally smaller so theyre perfect if you dont have much space to work with.";i:46;s:126:"Sometimes if you dont have an eat-in kitchen a bar-height table can provide a spot to eat that isnt in the formal dining room.";i:47;s:64:"These tables are sometimes referred to as regular dining tables.";i:48;s:92:"Its what you remember from meals at your parents house and probably your grandparents house.";i:49;s:55:"The table height is typically between 28 and 30 inches.";i:50;s:51:"The chair stool or bench height is 18 to 23 inches.";i:51;s:40:"The Advantage of Standard Height Dining.";i:52;s:24:"Dining Table Dimensions.";i:53;s:74:"Dining room tables have a pretty standard height range of 28 to 30 inches.";i:54;s:46:"Thats the size of a regular dining room table.";i:55;s:72:"Counters however are slightly taller and range between 34 and 36 inches.";i:56;s:61:"Furthermore bars are even taller at between 40 and 42 inches.";i:57;s:51:"The average width of an end table is between 16 22.";i:58;s:129:"When deciding on a side table be sure yours has a surface wide enough to hold any desired items like books plants or table lamps.";i:59;s:63:"Additionally leave a few inches between the end table and sofa.";i:60;s:23:"Shop Narrow End Tables.";}}